                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" id="aphid_sng_1" hclass="sense" fkcefr="c2"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">a very small insect that is harmful to plants. There are several types of <span class="dh">aphid</span>, including, for example, <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/greenfly" title="greenfly definition"><span class="ndv">greenfly</span></a>.</span></span><span class="topic-g"><span class="prefix">Topics </span><a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/topic/insects-worms-etc?level=c2" title="Topic insects-worms-etc"><span class="topic" href="l2:animals:insects_worms_etc?cefr=c2"><span class="topic_name">Insects, worms, etc.</span><span class="topic_cefr">c2</span></span></a></span><div class="collapse" htag="div" hclass="collapse"><span class="unbox" unbox="wordorigin" id="aphid_unbox_1"><span class="box_title">Word Origin</span><span class="body"><span class="p">late 19th cent.: back-formation from <span class="ei">aphides</span>, plural of <span class="ei">aphis</span> modern Latin, from Greek, perhaps a misreading of <span class="ei">koris</span> ‘bug’ (interpreting the characters κoρ ‘kor’ as αϕ ‘aph’).</span></span></span></div>    <div id="ring-links-box">
